{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-page-jsx","path":"/react/scheduler/docs/guides/appointments/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1 id=\"react-scheduler---appointments\"><a href=\"#react-scheduler---appointments\" aria-label=\"react scheduler   appointments permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>React Scheduler - Appointments</h1>\n<p>Our React Scheduler supports the following appointment types:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#one-time-appointments\">One-time appointments</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#zero-duration-appointments\">Zero-duration appointments</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#all-day-appointments\">All-day appointments</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#recurring-appointments\">Recurring appointments</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"related-plugins\"><a href=\"#related-plugins\" aria-label=\"related plugins permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Related Plugins</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"../reference/appointments.md\">Appointments</a> - renders appointments</li>\n<li><a href=\"../reference/all-day-panel.md\">AllDayPanel</a> - renders the all-day panel</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"one-time-appointments\"><a href=\"#one-time-appointments\" aria-label=\"one time appointments permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>One-Time Appointments</h2>\n<p>One-time appointments are those with specified start and end dates and times. They are shown in the following demo. To display one-time appointments on a view, add the <a href=\"../reference/appointments.md\">Appointments</a> plugin.</p>\n<p>.embedded-demo({ \"path\": \"scheduler-basic/day\", \"showThemeSelector\": true })</p>\n<h2 id=\"zero-duration-appointments\"><a href=\"#zero-duration-appointments\" aria-label=\"zero duration appointments permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Zero-Duration Appointments</h2>\n<p>Zero-duration appointments do not have an end time and date. They represent events without duration (reminders, arrival/departure time, and so on).</p>\n<p>To add a zero-duration appointment, specify the <code class=\"language-text\">startDate</code> in the <a href=\"../reference/scheduler.md#appointmentmodel\">AppointmentModel</a>, leave the <code class=\"language-text\">endDate</code> field unspecified, and add the <a href=\"../reference/appointments.md\">Appointments</a> plugin.</p>\n<p>.embedded-demo({ \"path\": \"scheduler-basic/zero-duration\", \"showThemeSelector\": true })</p>\n<h2 id=\"all-day-appointments\"><a href=\"#all-day-appointments\" aria-label=\"all day appointments permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>All-Day Appointments</h2>\n<p>All-day appointments last for the entire day or multiple days. They are displayed only in the <a href=\"../reference/month-view.md\">MonthView</a>. To display them in the day or week views, use the <a href=\"../reference/all-day-panel.md\">AllDayPanel</a> plugin.</p>\n<p>.embedded-demo({ \"path\": \"scheduler-all-day-panel/week-view\", \"showThemeSelector\": true })</p>\n<h2 id=\"recurring-appointments\"><a href=\"#recurring-appointments\" aria-label=\"recurring appointments permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Recurring Appointments</h2>\n<p>A recurring appointment is an appointment that is repeated after a specified time. An object that defines such an appointment should contain the <code class=\"language-text\">rRule</code> field whose value has the <a href=\"https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5545#section-3.8.5.3\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">iCalendar RRULE</a> format. To exclude specific dates from recurrence, specify the exceptions in the <code class=\"language-text\">exDate</code> field. Its values should have the <a href=\"https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5545#section-3.8.5.1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">iCalendar EXDATE</a> format.</p>\n<p>.embedded-demo({ \"path\": \"scheduler-recurrence/basic\", \"showThemeSelector\": true })</p>\n<h2 id=\"customize-the-appearance\"><a href=\"#customize-the-appearance\" aria-label=\"customize the appearance permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Customize the Appearance</h2>\n<p>The <a href=\"../reference/appointments.md\">Appointments</a> plugin allows you to customize the appearance of appointments. Override the plugin's <code class=\"language-text\">appointmentComponent</code> with a custom component. Use the <a href=\"../reference/appointments.md#appointmentsappointmentprops\">AppointmentProps</a> when you implement the custom component. The following example shows how to use this approach to add custom styles to appointments:</p>\n<p>.embedded-demo({ \"path\": \"scheduler-basic/simple-template\", \"showThemeSelector\": true })</p>","fields":{"technology":"react/scheduler","section":"docs"},"frontmatter":{"title":""}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"react/scheduler/docs/guides/appointments/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["3159585216","3662068265"]}